It's beautiful.

210
00:13:59,004 --> 00:14:01,672
Nice to see you both.
Isn't it something?

211
00:14:01,724 --> 00:14:03,241
Betty, you remember Trudy.

212
00:14:03,275 --> 00:14:05,476
Harry Crane. My wife Jennifer.

213
00:14:05,527 --> 00:14:07,812
Ken Cosgrove. We've... we've met.

214
00:14:07,863 --> 00:14:11,032
- Nice to see you all again.
- When are you due?

215
00:14:11,116 --> 00:14:13,151
Any minute. Can't you tell?

216
00:14:15,421 --> 00:14:17,288
Oh, that last month was the worse.

217
00:14:17,339 --> 00:14:20,258
- But of course this is your second.
- Uh, third.

218
00:14:20,292 --> 00:14:24,095
- How old is yours?
- Eight months. Beatrice Grace.

219
00:14:26,765 --> 00:14:28,433
Should we take a tour?

220
